ShortName: Multivariate normal distribution
Topic: probability
Concepts: extending the bell curve to multiple dimensions,
 the multivariate normal density formula,
 the covariance matrix as the shape of the data cloud (stretch and rotate),
 Mahalanobis distance (how many standard deviations away in all directions at once),
 marginal distributions of a multivariate normal are univariate normal,
 conditional distributions of a multivariate normal,
 generating multivariate normal samples in R
BuildsOn: [distributions-and-densities](distributions-and-densities/lesson.qmd),
 [mean-variance-covariance](mean-variance-covariance/lesson.qmd),
 [variance-structure-and-standardization](variance-structure-and-standardization/lesson.qmd),
 [matrices-and-linear-transforms](matrices-and-linear-transforms/lesson.qmd),
 [quadratic-forms-and-the-chi-square-statistic](quadratic-forms-and-the-chi-square-statistic/lesson.qmd)
